odel of a loyal proletariat thwarted Party efforts to construct a social and political order consistent with Bolshevik ideology. The conservative and coercive policies that Party leaders adopted in response, he argues, contributed to the Soviet Union's emergence as an authoritarian welfare state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aRural-urban migrationzRussia (Federation)zMoscowxHistoryy20th century. 0aUrbanizationzRussia (Federation)zMoscowxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorking classzRussia (Federation)zMoscowxHistoryy20th century. 4aHistory. 4aSoviet & East European History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172566140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501725661423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501725661/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles